    <h4>RULES FOR ADMISSION OF TY.BSC.IT</h4>
    <div class="container">
    <h5>Eligibility</h5>
        <p>	A student passing the H.S.C. Examination conducted by the Maharashtra State Board for Secondary and Higher Secondary Education, Mumbai Divisional Board in the SIX subjects specified below or from another equivalent Board of Secondary Education or any other statutory examining body, is eligible for admission to the First Year of the Senior college in Arts / Science/Commerce Course.

            (a) English
            (b) Any one of the Modern Indian Languages (Marathi/ Hindi)
            (c) Any four of the optional subjects for Arts, Sciences and Commerce courses as specified by the H.S.C. Board, Pune
            (d) The Application of an overseas student for admission to the college will be entertained only if it is forwarded with the recommendation letter of the Indian Diplomatic Mission in his / her country. Such applications must be accompanied by
            i) the final School / College Certificate Examination,
            ii) a testimonial from the Principal of the School / College regarding the character of the applicant, and
            iii) a provisional Eligibility Certificate issued by the University of Mumbai
            5. (d) For any change of stream there should be at least two common subjects between the previous stream and the stream of choice as per the provision of the Mumbai University circular. Thus a commerce student can change to Arts stream and a science student can opt for F.Y.B.Com/ F.Y.B.A. provided there are minimum 2 subjects from the Arts / Commerce.</p>
    <br />
        <h5>Documents to be submitted with Application Form:</h5>
        <p>1.	Documents required for student who has passed HSC examination of the Mumbai divisional Board:

            i) Original Mark sheet for H.S.C. Examination with a photocopy thereof,
            ii) College / School Leaving Certificate or NOC,</p>
        <p>2.	Documents required for student who has passed XII from Central Board of Secondary Education or the Indian School Certificate Examination or an equivalent examination:

            i) Original Mark sheet for H.S.C. Examination with a photocopy thereof,
            ii) College / School Leaving Certificate or NOC,
            iii) Provisional / Final Eligibility Certificate
            iv> any other Certificates that are deemed necessary</p>
        <p>3.	A student belonging to reserved category will have to submit a valid Caste Certificate as per the reservation policy of the Government along with the validity certificate wherever applicable and a non-creamy layer certificate.</p>

    <br />
    <br />
    
    
        <h4>RULES FOR MAINTAINING DISCIPLINE IN THE COLLEGE</h4>
    
        <h5>1. Attendance</h5>
        <p>1.	75% attendance at lectures/ practicals/tutorials is compulsory for all courses, as per the Ordinance 0.119, 0.120 issued by the University wide circular no.UG/235/98.</p>
        <p>2.	A learner who is not regular in attendance or fails to carry out his/ her work to the satisfaction of the Principal, is liable to cancellation of his/ her terms.</p>
        <p>3.	The learner who does not have minimum required attendance of 75 % of actual lectures/ practicals conducted in each semester or do not show satisfactory progress in semester / internal examinations will not be sent for college/ University examinations.</p>
        <p>4.	Periodical tests/ assignments/ seminars/ examination are compulsory for the learner of all classes.</p>
        <p>5.	A learner who remains absent for the periodical test/assignment/examination due to his/her illness shall be required to submit the medical certificate, along with the application endorsed by parent.</p>
        <p>6.	A learner who remains absent for the periodical test/assignment/examination due to NSS/NCC activity must intimate the Principal along with appropriate documents explaining his/her absence.</p>
        <p>7.	Learners who fail to maintain the condition of minimum attendance on account of bonafied illness, or any other reason which is deemed right by the Principal, should apply in writing to the Principal, for leave of absence, prior or within two days from the date of commencement of such failing which they will be treated as defaulters.</p>
        <p>8.	All applications for leave of absence along with medical certificate, if any, should be submitted to the Principal and not directly to any teacher.</p>
        <p>9.	Learners who are not permitted for the University examination will not be re-admitted to the college.</p>
        <p>10.	All decisions pertaining to grant of terms will be decided by an Attendance committee duly constituted by the college.</p>
            
        <br />
        <h5>2. Discipline</h5>
        <p>1.	Learners should always wear their valid college identity card whenever in the college or should be produced whenever demanded by any of the college staff. No learner is allowed to enter in the college premises without valid identity card.</p>
        <p>2.	Every learner is responsible to the college and should take utmost care of the college premises/ property/garden, plants. Any damage done to the property of the college is to be compensated either individually or collectively.</p>
        <p>3.	No person, other than college staff, can be invited to address any meeting or to participate in the college activity without prior permission of the Principal.</p>
        <p>4.	Learners should make themselves familiar with the college rules and regulations concerning them and also with regulations and notice issued by the college from time to time.</p>
        <p>6.	Smoking is strictly prohibited in the college premises.</p>

        <br />
        <h5>3. Mobile Phone</h5>
        <p>Bringing of mobiles within the campus is strictly prohibited as per the University norms .if any learner found using a mobile, the mobile set shall be forfeited and strict action shall be taken against the learner.</p>

        <br />
        <h5>4. Dress Code</h5>
        <p>The college does not enforce a dress code however learners are expected to preserve/ maintain the decorum of the college.</p>


